ZH: 我们需要在这里选出一位代表。
EN: We need to select a representative here.

ZH: 你为什么选了那本书？
EN: Why did you choose that book?

ZH: 选一件衣服以匹配你的新裤子。
EN: Select a piece of clothing to match your new pants.

ZH: 他在比赛中被选为队长。
EN: He was chosen as the captain in the match.

ZH: 我们需要选定一个日期来举办派对。
EN: We need to pick a date to have the party.

ZH: 她选了一种不同的颜色绘画。
EN: She chose a different color for the painting.

ZH: 选一个合适的时机告诉他这个好消息。
EN: Pick a right moment to tell him the good news.

ZH: 我不知道我应该选哪一个。
EN: I don't know which one I should choose.

ZH: 请从菜单中选一道你想吃的菜。
EN: Please select a dish you want to eat from the menu.

ZH: 选好你的座位，我们马上就要开始了。
EN: Choose your seat, we will start soon.

ZH: 她在选购礼物中花费了很多时间。
EN: She spent a lot of time selecting gifts.

ZH: 选一个合适的背包来装下你的物品。
EN: Choose a suitable backpack to carry your items.

ZH: 他被选为校长当然让他很自豪。
EN: Being chosen as the principal made him very proud.

ZH: 选一个适合你的运动鞋来锻炼。
EN: Choose a pair of sport shoes that fits you well for exercise.

ZH: 我很难在这些颜色中选一个。
EN: It's hard for me to choose one among these colors.

ZH: 我建议你选一个不同的方法尝试。
EN: I suggest you choose a different approach to try.

ZH: 选一条你认为适合的路线。
EN: Choose a route that you think is suitable.

ZH: 我们要在下个星期五选出新的班委。
EN: We will elect a new class committee next Friday.

ZH: 他拿起一本书，随意地选了一页开始阅读。
EN: He picked up a book and randomly selected a page to start reading.

ZH: 选好了东西记得回家。
EN: Don't forget to pick up your things before going home.
